'''National Parks of [[Haiti]]''' are places of natural or historical value designated for protection and sustainable utilization.
[[La Visite National Park]] and [[Pic Macaya National Park]] were the first two national parks to be established in [[Haiti]], both in 1983. They were created largely through the efforts of Charles A. Woods and colleagues.<ref>Woods CA, Ottenwalder JA. The natural history of southern Haiti. Florida Museum of Natural History, University of Florida; 1992</ref><ref>Woods CA, Sergile FE, Ottenwalder JA. Stewardship plan for the national parks and natural areas of Haiti. Florida Museum of Natural History, University of Florida; 1992.</ref> [[Grande Colline National Park]] was established on July 23, 2014,<ref>Le Moniteur, Journal Officiel de la Republique d’Haiti, No. 158, 21 August 2014</ref> and [[Grand Bois National Park]] and [[Deux Mamelles National Park]] were established on September 23, 2015.<ref name="LM10-8">Le Moniteur, Journal Officiel de la Republique d’Haiti, No. 193, 8 October 2015</ref> Those three recent parks were created largely through the efforts of [[S. Blair Hedges]] and Philippe Bayard.<ref>{{Cite web|title = A search for rare animals before Haiti's forests - and the animals - disappear|url = http://articles.philly.com/2011-09-13/news/30149741_1_rare-animals-frogs-forest|website = articles.philly.com|access-date = 2016-03-25}}</ref><ref name="HNT">{{cite web|author=Haiti National Trust |url=http://www.haititrust.org |title=Haiti National Trust |accessdate=2016-03-25}}</ref>
Current list of Haiti's national parks, not including [[List of marine parks and management areas in Haiti|marine parks and management areas in Haiti]]: *[[La Visite National Park]] *[[Pic Macaya National Park]] *[[Grande Colline National Park]] *[[Grand Bois National Park]] *[[Deux Mamelles National Park]] *National History Park – Citadelle, [[Sans-Souci Palace]] <ref>Le Moniteur, Journal Officiel de la Republique d’Haiti, No. 10, 16 January 2014</ref> *Parc National Naturel Foret des Pins <ref>Le Moniteur, Journal Officiel de la Republique d’Haiti, No. 10, 16 January 2014</ref> *[[Three Bays Protected Area|Three Bays National Park]] <ref>Le Moniteur, Journal Officiel de la Republique d’Haiti, No. 230, 11 December 2013</ref> *Île-à-Vache National Park <ref>Le Moniteur, Journal Officiel de la Republique d’Haiti, No. 156, 26 August 2013</ref> *National History Park – Matheux <ref name="LM10-8" />
