{{Infobox protected area | name = Sultan Reedy National Park | alt_name = ''Sultan Sazlığı Milli Parkı'' | iucn_category = | photo = Sultan sazlığı.jpg | photo_alt = | photo_caption = A view of [[Lake Yay]] and Sultan Reedy National Park. | photo_width = | map = Turkey | map_alt = | map_caption = | map_width = | relief = yes | label =Sultan Reedy NP | label_position = right | mark = | marker_size = | location = [[Yeşilhisar]]-[[Develi]]-[[Yahyalı]], [[Kayseri Province]], Turkey | nearest_city = | coords = {{coord|38|14|32|N|35|11|08|E|region:TR|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | coords_ref = | area = {{convert|24357|ha|abbr=on}} | designation = | authorized = | created = | established = {{start date|2006|03|17}} | designated = | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | visitation_ref = | governing_body = [[Ministry of Forest and Water Management (Turkey)|Ministry of Forest and Water Management]] | administrator = | operator = | owner = | world_heritage_site = | website = {{URL|http://www.milliparklar.gov.tr/mp/sultansazligi/index.htm}} | child = | embedded = {{Designation list | embed = yes | designation1 = Ramsar | designation1_offname = Sultan Marshes | designation1_date = 13 July 1994 | designation1_number = 661<ref>{{Cite web|title=Sultan Marshes|website=[[Ramsar Convention|Ramsar]] Sites Information Service|url=https://rsis.ramsar.org/ris/661|accessdate=25 April 2018}}</ref>}} }} '''Sultan Reedy National Park''' ({{lang-tr|Sultan Sazlığı Milli Parkı}}), {{aka}} '''Sultan Marshes''', established on March 17, 2006, is a [[national park]] in central Turkey. It is located around [[Lake Yay]] between the [[Yeşilhisar]], [[Develi]] and [[Yahyalı]] districts of [[Kayseri Province]].<ref name="mp"/> It was designated a [[Ramsar site]] on July 13, 1994.
It covers an area of {{convert|24357|ha|abbr=on}} at {{convert|1000|m|ft|abbr=on}} above main sea level.<ref name="mp"/>
